27namespace ZXing {
28namespace MaxiCode {
29
30
31/**
32* This method detects a code in a "pure" image -- that is, pure monochrome image
33* which contains only an unrotated, unskewed, image of a code, with some white border
34* around it. This is a specialized method that works exceptionally fast in this special
35* case.
36*/
37static BitMatrix ExtractPureBits(const BitMatrix& image)
38{
39 int left, top, width, height;
40 if (!image.findBoundingBox(left, top, width, height, BitMatrixParser::MATRIX_WIDTH)) {
41 return {};
42 }
43
44 // Now just read off the bits
45 BitMatrix result(BitMatrixParser::MATRIX_WIDTH, BitMatrixParser::MATRIX_HEIGHT);
46 for (int y = 0; y < BitMatrixParser::MATRIX_HEIGHT; y++) {
47 int iy = top + (y * height + height / 2) / BitMatrixParser::MATRIX_HEIGHT;
48 for (int x = 0; x < BitMatrixParser::MATRIX_WIDTH; x++) {
49 int ix = left + (x * width + width / 2 + (y & 0x01) * width / 2) / BitMatrixParser::MATRIX_WIDTH;
50 if (image.get(ix, iy)) {
51 result.set(x, y);
52 }
53 }
54 }
55 return result;
56}
57
58Reader::Reader(const DecodeHints& hints) : _isPure(hints.isPure()) {}
59
60Result
61Reader::decode(const BinaryBitmap& image) const
62{
63 auto binImg = image.getBlackMatrix();
64 if (binImg == nullptr) {
65 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
66 }
67
68 //TODO: this only works with effectively 'pure' barcodes. Needs proper detector.
69 BitMatrix bits = ExtractPureBits(*binImg);
70 if (bits.empty()) {
71 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
72 }
73
74 return Result(Decoder::Decode(bits), {}, BarcodeFormat::MAXICODE);
75}
